<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<subsection xml:id="ch5-section-expanding-acceleration-subsection-all" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Putting everything together</title>

    <p>
        The acceleration of an air parcel in <xref ref="eqn-total-derivative-spherical-start" text="type-global" /> expands into
    </p>

    <p>
        <md>
            <mrow>
                 \frac{D\vec{u}}{Dt}
                 \amp = 
                \left(
                    \frac{Du}{Dt} \, \hat{i}
                    + \frac{Dv}{Dt} \, \hat{j}
                    + \frac{Dw}{Dt} \, \hat{k}
                \right)
                +
                \left(
                    u \, \frac{D \hat{i}}{Dt}
                    + v \, \frac{D \hat{j}}{Dt}
                    + w \, \frac{D \hat{k}}{Dt}
                \right)
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
                \amp = 
                \frac{Du}{Dt} \, \hat{i}
                + \frac{Dv}{Dt} \, \hat{j}
                + \frac{Dw}{Dt} \, \hat{k}
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
                \amp \quad
                +
                u \left(
                    \frac{u}{a \cos{\phi}} (\hat{j} \, \sin{\phi} - \hat{k} \, \cos{\phi})
                \right)
                +
                v \left(
                    -\frac{u \tan{\phi}}{a} \, \hat{i}
                    -\frac{v}{a} \, \hat{k}
                \right)
                +
                w \left(
                    \frac{u}{a} \, \hat{i}
                    + \frac{v}{a} \, \hat{j}
                \right)
            </mrow>
            <mrow xml:id="eqn-total-derivative-spherical-final" number="yes">
                \amp =
                \left(
                    \frac{Du}{Dt}
                    + \frac{uw}{a}
                    - \frac{uv \tan{\phi}}{a}
                \right) \hat{i}
                +
                \left(
                    \frac{Dv}{Dt}
                    + \frac{vw}{a}
                    + \frac{u^2 \tan{\phi}}{a}
                \right) \hat{j}
                +
                \left(
                    \frac{Dw}{Dt}
                    - \frac{u^2 + v^2}{a}
                \right) \hat{k}
            </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>

    <p>
        when applied to the spherical Earth.
        The "extra" terms inversely proportional to <m>a</m> are called <term>curvature terms</term>,
        and the above derivations show that they result from Earth's sphericity.
        Specifically,
        they are caused by Earth's surface curving away underneath the straight-line trajectory of <m>\vec{u}</m>.
    </p>

</subsection>